<H1> Stephen R. (Steve) Schach </H1> 
<H3>Associate Professor of Computer Science and Computer Engineering </H3> 
<HR>

Steve Schach obtained the M.S. degree in Physics at the
<!WA1><A HREF = "http://wissgi.weizmann.ac.il"> Weizmann Institute of Science</A>
in 1972, and the Ph.D. in Applied Mathematics at the
<!WA2><A HREF ="http://www.uct.ac.za"> University of Cape Town</A>
in 1973.  
<P>
Between 1972 and 1983, Professor Schach held faculty positions
in the Departments of Applied Mathematics and Computer Science at the 
University of Cape Town.
In 1978/9 he spent a sabbatical year at the Weizmann Institute of
Science.
In 1983 he joined the 
<!WA3><A HREF="http://cswww.vuse.vanderbilt.edu/">
Department of Computer Science</A> at Vanderbilt University.
<P>
Professor Schach's 
<!WA4><A HREF = "http://cswww.vuse.vanderbilt.edu/~srs/soft-eng.html"> research interests</A> 
are in the field of software
engineering, and particularly in object-oriented software
engineering.  He and his
<!WA5><A HREF = "http://cswww.vuse.vanderbilt.edu/~srs/soft-eng.html#gradstuds"> research students</A> 
are investigating issues relating the object-oriented paradigm.
He also leads 
<!WA6><A HREF="http://cswww.vuse.vanderbilt.edu/~jgray/sdg.html">
SDG++</A>, the software engineering discussion group.

<P>
Dr. Schach has written a number of 
<!WA7><A HREF = "http://cswww.vuse.vanderbilt.edu/~srs/books.html"> textbooks</A> on software engineering and
object-oriented software engineering.  He has over 80 
<!WA8><A HREF = "http://cswww.vuse.vanderbilt.edu/~srs/references.html"> refereed publications</A> to his name,
including
<!WA9><A HREF = "http://cswww.vuse.vanderbilt.edu/~srs/references.html#videotapes"> refereed videotapes</A>.

Dr. Schach 
<!WA10><A HREF = "http://cswww.vuse.vanderbilt.edu/~srs/consulting.html"> consults</A> and teaches short
courses internationally on
software engineering topics, including reuse, CASE, and the
object-oriented paradigm.
<P>
He is married to Sharon M. Stein, M.D., Associate Professor of 
<!--A HREF = "http://www.mc.vanderbilt.edu/vumcdept/radio.html"-->
Pediatric Radiology <!--/A--> at 
<!WA11><A HREF ="http://www.mc.vanderbilt.edu/main.html"> 
Vanderbilt University Medical Center</A>. 
They have two children.  
<!WA12><A HREF = "http://www.columbia.edu/~dms59/"> David</A> 
is a sophomore studying Chemical Engineering at 
<!WA13><A HREF = "http://www.cc.columbia.edu/index.html"> Columbia
University</A>, and Lauren is in the eleventh grade at the
<!WA14><A HREF = "http://www.university-sch.davidson.k12.tn.us">
University School of Nashville</A>.
<P>
Steve's hobbies include writing <!WA15><A HREF = "http://cswww.vuse.vanderbilt.edu/~srs/books.html">books</A> 
and <!WA16><A HREF = "http://www.vtourist.com/vt/"> travel</A>.

